    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> Dei gracia
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Quia divini muneris nutu regni
                        gubernacula reguntur, nullaque potestas nisi a Deo procedit, pro certo
                        regalem omnino eius decet excellenciam, ut ea que, Deo largiente, suscepit,
                        pro suorum fidelium commodo impartire studeat, ut dum eorum precibus
                        benignitatis sue aures acommodat eos in suo obsequi devociores efficiat,
                        insuper ab eterno remuneratore premia sine fine mansura percipiat. Idcirco
                        omnium sancte Dei Ecclesie nostrorumque fidelium presencium scilicet ac
                        futurorum comperiat industria, eo quod <persName key="#Medici #Abbots"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName> vir probus ac
                        prudentissimus <rs key="#Medici">medicus</rs> noster <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbas</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/120">monasterii Sancte
                            Cristine</orgName> prope <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/139"
                            >curtem nostram <placeName key="#Curtes #Monasteries" ref="#places/342"
                                >Ollonam</placeName></geogName> sive per <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Consiliarius_regis #Bishops" ref="#people/58"
                            >Petrum</persName> venerabilem <rs key="#Bishops">episcopum</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Intercessory #Consiliarius_regis"><name ref="Restaldus"
                                >Restaldum</name></persName> et per <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Marquis/duke #Consiliarius_regis"><name
                                ref="Aschericus">Ascherium</name></persName> illustrem <rs
                            key="#Marquis/duke">marchionem</rs> summos <rs key="#Consiliarius_regis"
                            >consciliarios</rs> nostros expetiis <rs key="#Intercessory"
                            >clemenciam</rs> nostram, ut ei quandam <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >curtem iuris regni nostri</rs> nomine <geogName
                            key="#Houses #Natural_landscape #Rivers #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Forests #Mills #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#estates/141">Bellamium</geogName> in <rs key="#Comitatus"
                            >comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/142"><placeName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#places/2795">Aquinense</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus
                        pertinenciis et adiacenciis suis in integrum, <rs
                            key="#Houses"
                            >casis</rs> videlicet, <rs
                            key="#Fruits/vegetables"
                            >ortis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>, <rs>pascuis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, <rs key="#Landed_possessions">cultis et
                            incultis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Forests"
                            >silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fruits/vegetables"
                            >arboribus pomiferis et impomiferis</rs>, <rs key="#Mountains"
                            >montibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Natural_landscape"
                            > vallibus, planitiebus, ripis, rupinis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis et aquarum decursibus</rs>, seu <rs
                            key="#Mills"
                            >molendinis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Royal_slave"
                            >servis quoque et ancillis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldionibus et aldianis</rs> concedere dignaremur. Cuius precibus
                        libenter adquiescentes hoc nostrum preceptum fieri iussimus, per quod
                        predictam curtem cum omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis prefato
                        Iohanni abbati vel successoribus ipsius <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >proprietario iure</rs> concedimus et perdonamus, ut habeat, teneat
                        atque possideat, tam ipse quam et successores eius, faciatque exinde
                        quicquid eius decreverit animus. Confirmamus ei <rs key="#Immunity"
                            >potestate tenendi, possidendi, donandi, vendendi, commutandi seu in
                            qualibet ipsius loci necessitate alienandi, remota cuiuslibet publice
                            potestatis inquietudine ac molestatione</rs>. Confirmamus insuper atque
                        concedimus eidem Iohanni abbati eiusque successoribus terram circa ipsum
                        monasterium positam imperatorum, regum seu quorumlibet potestatum fideli
                        renovacione collatam cum tutela servanda, ab oriente <rs
                            key="#Lakes"
                            >lacus qui dicitur Sussinate</rs> cum tota <placeName ref="#places/298"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Vallinata</placeName> in integrum usque in <rs key="#Rivers"
                        >Padum</rs>, a meridie <rs
                            key="#Ports"
                            >portus qui vocatur Novus</rs> cum rochalibus supera, ab occidente vero
                        a curte nostra Ollona dividitur, a septentrione igitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/278"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terra <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/53">Sancti Systi</orgName> que
                            nuncupatur <geogName ref="#estates/113">Yberni</geogName></placeName> et
                        extenditur usque ad <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium Lambrum</rs> et <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Victumlongum</placeName> atque <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Castellum Desertum</placeName> et usque ad <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >fontanam Sancti Ambrosii</placeName> et <placeName ref="#places/299"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Brionem</placeName> et totus insuper <placeName ref="#places/277"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Monsmallus</placeName> usque in predicta Vallinata. Si quis autem
                        contra hoc nostrum preceptum quandocumque insurgere temptaverit, sciat se
                        compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">triginta libras auri obrizi</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">medietatem palacio nostro</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem prefato abbati
                            eiusque successoribus</rs>. Ut autem ab omnibus verius credatur et
                        diligencius observetur, manu propria subtus confirmavimus et anuli nostri
                        impressione insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Berengarii serenissimi regis.
                            <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Restaldus"
                            >Restaldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> iussione regia ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/58">Petri</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor">archicancellari</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. Dat.
                        Kal. Decembris, anno incarnationis Domini DCCCXCVIII, anno vero regni domani
                        Berengarii gloriosissimi regis XII, indicione secunda. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/191">Regia</placeName> civitate. In Dei nomine feliciter,
                        amen. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
